He who passes through this gate must give up all hope.
>It is the gateway to hell in the third song of the Inferno in the epic poem "The Divine Comedy" by the 13th-14th century Italian poet, [Dante] Alighieri.
>It is well known for its inscription, "He who passes through this gate must give up all hope," which is also used to express deep despair.
	[https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/地獄の門 Gates of Hell - Wikipedia]
 Rodin's "[The Thinker]" sits atop this [Gates of Hell].
